<br>
That said.   How can a person who feels so low ask for help?  How many times have you asked for help to have your friends say :  OH I am too busy right now.<br>
Or:    No that is too depressing I have better things to do.<br>
<br>
There are many reasons a person may want to commit suicide.  Major Depressive disorder is a physiological disorder (that means it is physical not mental and can be treated with drugs) that affects 50% of the population over the course of their life.  The wish to end it all is not something they have any control over at all.  It is biological.  These people need anti-depressants to combat this as well as psychological counselling and support.<br>
<br>
Other conditions can also motivate the will to end it all.  A person who has other illnesses - chronic pain, Schizophrenia, end stages of cancer etc.  People with Borderline personality disorder will often claim they wish to commit suicide but usually abort there attempts as they are crying for help out of the deep pain that is within there pysche.  These people cannot be treated with medication as their wish is psychological and they need to be treated psychologically.  This is only a summary intended to show that this is not a simple thing that can be diagnosed on a chat forum.  <br>
<br>
Is it hard to ask for help when you are at your lowest ebb?  when you feel like utter shite?  <br>
<br>
Yes it is.  The time when you need the help the most is when you feel the least able to take a rejection.  <br>
<br>
Please do not offer empty promises of help.  If you promise to be there for someone -do it.<br>
<br>
I am writing this because I care about Shintou whose writings give me pleasure (although not this one)  as his sense of humor really touches me.  <br>
<br>
Who deserves to live??  Certainly someone with Shintou's talent does.  We should try to preserve people who have something to offer and let the ones with no ablitity to empathise go.  IMO<br>
<br>
People of talent in history who suffered from suicidal ideation or mental illness:  Many of our greatest actors and actresses suffered from Depression.  Kurt Cobain killed himself - I miss Nirvana.<br>
Winston Churchill suffered from Bipolar Disorder (manic-depression)  there are others but I cant recall their names at present.<br>
